Draagdim fo Elpmet Eht~
   Broken and stained once-white tile covered with troughs and ruts where the
gold scrollwork has been clawed and scratched out dot the otherwise barren land-
scape of the temple floor. Columns extend upward, gnarled and shattered obelisks
of a dark desolate stone. The eerie not-light of Draagdim gives a few splotchy
patches of respite from the suffocating darkness of this place.
   To the north, an uneven and cracked stair extends down to a empty square. To
the south is a dilapidated and forgotten altar. To the west is an abandoned shop
and to the east is the great pit where lost adventurers scrabble and fight for
morsels.
