#19901
Ratla Elpmet Eth Yb~
   The shattered remnants of a monument to some meaningless entity fill the
room. Overhead, the not-sky is visible through the broken vaulted ceiling, held
aloft by cracked and mangled columns of stone that appear ready to collapse. A
single chandelier hangs askew, coated in shimmering blue-green cobwebs, its
comrades in pieces upon the floor.
   Dull, scuffed floors lead back north to the temple. In the other cardinal
directions stand giant piles of stone, debris and thick cobwebs blocking all
passage.
~
